# **âœ… HIVE AFFILIATION LAYER â€” FINAL WHITEPAPER (v1)**

---

## **ğŸ§  PURPOSE**

Affiliation is how students **align with identity structures** inside HIVEâ€”not through bios, chats, or forms, but through **lightweight behavioral signals**.

It governs how students:

- Orbit and explore without pressure
- Join and shape emerging cultures
- Progress from Seeker to Builder
- Leave a Trail of meaningful participation

Spaces are the universal identity field. **Everything is a Space**â€”whether itâ€™s a club, scene, subculture, or ritual cohort.

---

## **ğŸ¯ CORE GOALS**

1. **Let students affiliate softly** before committing
2. **Reflect identity through motion** (not static profile data)
3. **Give Builders real member clarity** without noise
4. **Structure affiliation tiers invisibly**, not as social performance
5. **Ensure every affiliation has systemic impact**

---

## **ğŸ§± KEY BEHAVIORS + SURFACES**

| **Surface** | **Behavior** | **System Effect** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Feed Suggestion | Tap / linger | Adds curiosity weight; triggers Observer |
| Join Button | Tap | Adds Member status; Trail + Gravity start |
| Join Button | Long-press | Adds to Watchlist; soft affiliation |
| Space Content | Repost / RSVP | Triggers Active tier |
| Reaffirmation Strip | â€œStill vibing?â€ | Adjusts Trail/Gravity based on response |
| Feed Echo | Multiple Space taps | Suggests formal Join / Watch |

All interactions handled via **Feed, Rituals, or Strip**. No new tabs or overlays.

---

## **ğŸ” INVISIBLE TIERED AFFILIATION**

| **Tier** | **Trigger** | **Meaning** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Observer | 3+ passive touches (taps, lingers, hovers) | Curiosity detected |
| Member | Taps Join | Starts Trail + Feed/Space weighting |
| Active | Posts, RSVPs, rituals inside Space | High Gravity; shown in Builder Dashboard |
| Dormant | 14+ days inactivity | Downweighted affiliation |
| Dropped | 21+ days no action or ritual â€œGhostedâ€ | Trail archived; removed from weighting |

---

## **ğŸ”„ SYSTEM ENGINE CONNECTIONS**

| **Engine** | **Role in Affiliation** |
| --- | --- |
| Trail | Tracks affiliation history and reentry cues |
| Gravity | Determines interest between user â†” Space |
| Cluster | Suggests related Spaces + proximity |
| Role | Classifies user state (Observer â†’ Active) |
| Feed | Adjusts surface weighting based on affiliation tier |

---

## **ğŸ”§ AFFILIATION UX FLOW**

1. **Seeker sees Space in Feed**
    - Taps once â†’ nothing happens yet
    - Taps twice â†’ system tags as Observer
2. **Seeker taps Join**
    - Trail starts
    - Feed and Rituals adjust weighting
    - Builder sees Member increase
3. **Seeker interacts in Space (RSVP/repost)**
    - Becomes Active
    - System logs high-affinity
    - Role Engine locks in contribution status
4. **System checks back after 2 weeks**
    - â€œStill vibing with [Space]?â€
    - Yes â†’ gravity boost
    - Ghosting â†’ Trail fade begins
5. **Multiple Space alignments**
    - System prompts:
        
        â€œOther students in [X] are watching [Y]â€
        
    - Cross-Space identity begins forming

---

## **ğŸ§¬ DESIGN PRINCIPLES**

- **No social pressure**
- **No profile editing**
- **No fake engagement layers**
- **Motion = identity**
- **You can belong without declaring it**

---

## **ğŸ§  WHY THIS MATTERS**

Without this layer:

- Builders get false signals
- Seekers remain invisible
- System canâ€™t reflect or evolve cultural dynamics
- Discovery breaks into chaos

With this layer:

- Cultural alignment becomes trackable
- System can loop students into belonging
- Builders can create Spaces that liveâ€”even with silent users

# **âœ… HIVE PARTICIPATION LAYER â€” INTERNAL WHITEPAPER (v1)**

---

## **ğŸ§  PURPOSE**

The Participation Layer defines **how students take visible actions** within HIVE.

Participation is not content. It is **behavior that alters system state.**

This layer creates:

- Input signals (RSVP, Drop, Vote, Repost)
- Group energy (Spaces stay warm, events gain traction)
- System feedback (Feed reweights, Pulse ignites, Trail deepens)

If no one participates, the system dies.

---

## **ğŸ” PRIMARY GOAL**

Build a structure where **every action is lightweight, expressive, and consequential**.

This layer must work for:

- Active students
- Lurkers
- Dead orgs
- Pre-seeded events with zero context

---

## **ğŸ”§ SUPPORTED PARTICIPATION TYPES**

| **Action** | **Description** | **Location** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Drop** | 1-line post inside a Space. No replies. | Space |
| **RSVP** | Tap to attend an event. | Feed / Event |
| **Repost** | Share content to Feed. | Feed / Space |
| **Quote** | Repost with a 1-line comment. | Feed / Space |
| **Vote** | Tap to respond to a poll. | Space |
| **Boost** | Highlight a Drop to top (Builder-only). | Space |
| **Watch** | Soft-follow a Space or event. | Feed / Space |
| *(v1.1)* **React** | Tap-to-signal interest (e.g. ğŸ”¥ ğŸ‘€). | Feed (optional) |

---

## **ğŸ§¬ SYSTEM OUTPUT FROM PARTICIPATION**

| **Action** | **Triggers** | **System Effect** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Drop | Trail, Pulse | Keeps Space alive; may surface in Feed |
| RSVP | Trail, Pulse | Event gets Feed priority; Feed reorders |
| Repost | Pulse, Feed | Boosts visibility to others |
| Quote | Pulse, Feed | Creates new Feed card |
| Vote | Trail, Feed tuning | Signals active member; drives Feed logic |
| Boost | Feed surfacing | Pins Drop to top of Space; visible in Feed |
| Watch | Trail, Gravity | Adjusts personalization and Feed recs |

---

## **ğŸ—‚ CARD LIFECYCLE LOGIC (DECAY + EXTENSION)**

Cards decay if untouched. System avoids clutter by default.

| **Card Type** | **Default Lifespan** | **Extensions** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Drop | 48h | Boost +24h; Quote +12h |
| Event | Until start time | RSVP resets decay window |
| Poll | Set by Builder | Votes extend visibility |
| Quote | 24h | Requotes add time |
| Boosted Card | 6h pinned | One boost per post |

System decays posts softly (fade in color, drop to bottom). Trail stores all for system memory, not UI clutter.

---

## **ğŸ§  FEEDBACK LOOPS**

Every interaction must produce a reaction.

| **Action** | **User Feedback** |
| --- | --- |
| Drop | Post appears instantly; may be Boosted |
| RSVP | RSVP tag shown; triggers possible Strip nudge |
| Repost | Feed echoes ripple to others |
| Quote | New Feed card appears (sometimes with view count) |
| Vote | Sees poll results (post-vote) |
| Boost | Card moves to top; labeled â€œBoostedâ€ |

There are **no silent actions except Watch**.

---

## **ğŸ•¹ UX DESIGN RULES**

- Every participation option is **1-step max**
- No modals with >1 input
- No threading, replies, or infinite comments
- Participation creates **modular cards**, not content streams
- System must visibly respond (card moves, Feed changes, Strip updates)

---

## **ğŸ“² MOBILE IMPLEMENTATION NOTES**

| **Gesture** | **Result** |
| --- | --- |
| Tap RSVP / Vote | Logs instantly, triggers feedback |
| Tap â€œDropâ€ | Opens 1-line input modal |
| Tap Repost | Sends original to userâ€™s Feed |
| Long-press (Builder) | Triggers Boost |
| Tap Quote | Opens quote input â†’ creates new Feed card |

---

## **âœ… LAYER COMPLETE WHEN:**

- Every action feeds back into the system
- No participation feels dead-end
- Students feel presence without needing comments or likes
- Builders donâ€™t have to post daily to keep Spaces warm
- Every RSVP, Drop, Quote or Vote moves something

# **âœ… HIVE CREATION LAYER â€” INTERNAL WHITEPAPER (v1)**

---

## **ğŸ§  PURPOSE**

The Creation Layer defines how new objects â€” **Spaces**, **Events**, and **Rituals** â€” are introduced into the system.

