- Fast
- Mobile-first
- Behavior-driven
- Feed-integrated

No dashboards. No forms. Only inputs that create motion.

---

## **ğŸ“¦ OBJECTS THAT CAN BE CREATED**

| **Object** | **Who Creates It** | **Surface** | **Purpose** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Space** | Any student | Feed â†’ Space Tab | Starts a new affiliation node |
| **Event** | Builder only, or auto-promoted Drop | Inside Space | Creates group convergence |
| **Ritual** | Builder (inside HiveLab) | HiveLab â†’ Feed | Social interaction scaffolding |

---

## **ğŸ”¹ 1. SPACE CREATION**

### **âœ… Flow: â€œName it. Tag it. Done.â€**

- Inputs:
    - Space name
    - Select 1â€“2 tags from system library
- Optional:
    - 1-liner description
    - Emoji or logo (default = system icon)

### **ğŸ“² UX Location:**

- From â€œ+â€ button on Spaces screen
- From prompt in Feed (e.g. â€œWant to start your own?â€)

### **ğŸ” Visibility Logic:**

| **State** | **Criteria** | **Feed/Search Visibility** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Hidden | Created | Only visible to creator |
| Forming | 3 joins + 1 Drop | Searchable, system-suggested |
| Live | 10+ joins + active Drops/Events | Eligible for Feed surface, Boost, Pulse |
| Dormant | No activity 7d | Soft-hidden, archive path |
| Legacy | Archived | Trail-only memory |

### **ğŸ” System Actions:**

- Assign creator as Builder (behind-the-scenes role)
- Track all member motion via Trail
- Builder can Boost Drops or create Events/Rituals

---

## **ğŸ”¹ 2. EVENT CREATION**

### **âœ… Flow A: Builder-Initiated Event**

Tap â€œCreate Eventâ€ inside a Space

- Inputs:
    - Title
    - Time
    - Location
    - Optional context / description
- Events belong to Spaces
- Only Builders can initiate

---

### **âœ… Flow B: Event-As-Post**

A student Drops: â€œmovie night @ 8pm, my placeâ€

- 3+ people tap â€œGoing?â€
    
    â†’ System auto-converts Drop to Event
    
    â†’ Appears in Space and Feed
    

**Promotes organic mobilization** without forcing Builders to structure everything.

---

### **ğŸ” Event Visibility Logic:**

| **State** | **Criteria** | **System Behavior** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Draft | Created, no RSVP | Visible only in Space |
| Live | 1+ RSVP | Visible to Space members |
| Feed-Surfaceable | 5+ RSVP or Boost | Appears in Feed |
| Expired | After event time passes | Archived into Trail |

---

### **ğŸ” System Actions:**

- RSVP logs Trail entry
- Repost or Quote triggers Pulse
- Event can be Boosted if 1+ RSVP
- Events may be auto-linked to Rituals

---

## **ğŸ”¹ 3. RITUAL CREATION (BUILDER, VIA Hivelab)**

### **âœ… Rituals are created inside HiveLab by Builders**

- E.g. Polls, challenges, confessions, one-liner prompts
- Each Ritual is limited-time, participation-based
- Results feed back into Feed â†’ triggers motion

---

### **ğŸ“² Example Flows:**

- Builder selects: â€œRun a pollâ€
- Inputs question + 2â€“5 options
- System runs Ritual for 24â€“48h
- After close, results appear as Feed card:
    
    â€œIn Design Union, 72% voted for â€˜Chaos Nightâ€™â€
    

---

### **ğŸ” System Actions:**

- Vote = Trail signal
- Result = Pulse input
- Feed surfaces winning option or cultural sentiment

---

## **ğŸ”’ SYSTEM GUARDRAILS**

| **System** | **Purpose** |
| --- | --- |
| **Thresholds** | Prevent Feed spam (e.g. min 3 joins before Space is visible) |
| **Auto-Archive** | Decays Events, Spaces, or Rituals with no interaction |
| **Role Logic** | Builders manage Boosts, Events, Rituals |
| **Repost + Quote Integration** | All creations can be echoed into Feed |

